      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 25th June 1888. ¶ The honorable Alfred Deakin M.L.A., ¶ Chief Secretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.06.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alfred Deakin </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">L88/6183, unit 350, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof. PS. 28/8/08.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25th June 1888.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable Alfred Deakin M.L.A.,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to report, that the Iconography of the Australian Acacias<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.13.01.</p>
               </note> is now completed, though in course of time, as new material accumulates, a supplement will have to appear. As it is desirable, that this series of works, comprising a hitherto the Eucalypts, the Myoporinae and the Acacias, should be continued a lithographic artist having been purposely trained who labors by piece-work, I would beg your permission that in the new financial year the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Salsolaceae</hi>
               </seg> may be illustrated, as the Saltbushes of Australia being so very important for pastural purposes. The sums kindly placed by you on the estimates, for my branch of the service, will suffice for bringing out the proposed new volume of these illustrations.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">notes are a bit scrambled but it appears that Deakin approved M's request re the illustrations on 9 July 1888.</seg> On 9 July T. Wilson, Under Secretary, forwarded the file to M so that he could 'note approval. I understand there is sufficient provision already on his Estimates for the current financial year'. M replied the next day 'with best thanks no extra means required'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">there is a note 'Gov. Bot, 28/6/88 - was a note sent to M before these minutes were made??</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your very obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
